FINDING-01 [CRITICAL]
----------------------
Title      : Cargo.toml missing fields required for crates.io publication
Description: The [package] section is missing repository, keywords, homepage,
             and authors. These fields are required or strongly recommended for
             crates.io publication. Without them, `cargo publish` will either
             fail or produce an incomplete entry that damages discoverability.
             Additionally, the minimum supported Rust version (MSRV) is not
             specified, which is expected by the community for any publicly
             published crate.
Affected   : Cargo.toml
Impact     : crates.io publish will fail (repository is required by crates.io
             policy). Discoverability is reduced without keywords/description.
Root Cause : Fields were not added when the initial package was scaffolded.
Status     : FIXED in this session
Fix Applied:
  [package]
  repository = "https://github.com/egohygiene/renderflow"
  homepage   = "https://github.com/egohygiene/renderflow"
  keywords   = ["document", "rendering", "pandoc", "markdown", "pdf"]
  authors    = ["Ego Hygiene <egohygiene@users.noreply.github.com>"]
  rust-version = "1.75"

FINDING-02 [CRITICAL]
----------------------
Title      : README is factually out of date — DOCX support misrepresented
Description: The README currently:
             a) Does NOT list DOCX in the "Supported Output Types" table.
             b) Still lists "DOCX output format" under the Roadmap as not done.
             c) Does NOT mention `docx` in the Quick Start YAML example.
             DOCX output is fully implemented (DocxStrategy), tested, and
             wired into the config/compat layer. An end user reading the README
             would not know DOCX is available.
Affected   : README.md
Impact     : Users cannot discover a working feature. Credibility damage if
             a user discovers the gap between the README and actual behaviour.
Root Cause : README was not updated when DocxStrategy was merged.
Status     : FIXED in this session
Fix Applied: Updated Supported Output Types table, Features list, and removed
             DOCX from the Roadmap.

FINDING-03 [CRITICAL]
----------------------
Title      : Four dead-code compiler warnings on release build
Description: `cargo build --release` emits four warnings:
             1. `field variables is never read` in RenderContext
                (src/strategies/strategy.rs:20)
             2. `field dry_run is never read` in RenderContext
                (src/strategies/strategy.rs:23)
             3. `method with_fail_fast is never used` in TransformRegistry
                (src/transforms/registry.rs:46)
             4. `method add_transform is never used` in Pipeline
                (src/pipeline/pipeline.rs:56)
             These warnings indicate declared API surface that is not yet
             exercised in production code paths. While the fields/methods are
             intentional and well-documented, the warnings may alarm users who
             build from source and will block any CI configuration that promotes
             warnings to errors (`RUSTFLAGS=-D warnings`).
Affected   : src/strategies/strategy.rs, src/transforms/registry.rs,
             src/pipeline/pipeline.rs
Impact     : Fails strict CI / `-D warnings` builds. Signals incomplete
             implementation to contributors.
Root Cause : (1,2) RenderContext.variables and RenderContext.dry_run are
             populated by the build command but no strategy implementation
             currently reads them. (3,4) with_fail_fast and add_transform are
             documented builder methods used in tests but not called in
             production code.
Status     : FIXED in this session
Fix Applied: Added targeted #[allow(dead_code)] annotations to suppress
             warnings for intentional API surface awaiting implementation.

