FINDING-04 [WARNING]
---------------------
Title      : No release profile optimisation in Cargo.toml
Description: Cargo.toml has no [profile.release] section. Consequently the
             release binary uses default optimisation settings:
             - No LTO (link-time optimisation) → larger binary size
             - codegen-units = 16 → less aggressive optimisation
             - No symbol stripping → larger binary
             These defaults are fine for development but suboptimal for
             distributed binaries.
Affected   : Cargo.toml
Impact     : Binary size and runtime performance are not at their maximum for
             external distribution.
Root Cause : [profile.release] was never configured.
Status     : FIXED in this session
Fix Applied:
  [profile.release]
  opt-level     = 3
  lto           = true
  codegen-units = 1
  strip         = true
  panic         = "abort"

FINDING-05 [WARNING]
---------------------
Title      : No automated GitHub Release workflow
Description: There is no .github/workflows/release.yml (or equivalent).
             Pre-built binaries for Linux (x86_64 + aarch64), macOS, and
             Windows are referenced in the README installation section, but
             there is no automation to produce them on a version tag push.
             Cross.toml exists and documents the supported cross-compilation
             targets, but the workflow to use it on release is missing.
Affected   : .github/workflows/ (missing file)
Impact     : Every release requires a manual developer action. The README
             instructions for "Download from GitHub Releases" point to
             artefacts that do not exist yet.
Root Cause : Release automation was not added.
Status     : NOT FIXED — tracked as follow-up
Suggested Fix:
  Create .github/workflows/release.yml that:
  - triggers on `push: tags: ['v*']`
  - builds release binaries for x86_64-unknown-linux-musl,
    aarch64-unknown-linux-musl, x86_64-apple-darwin, x86_64-pc-windows-msvc
  - creates a GitHub Release and uploads the binaries as assets

