FINDING-08 [MINOR]
-------------------
Title      : RenderContext.variables and .dry_run are never used by strategies
Description: The OutputStrategy::render interface accepts a RenderContext that
             includes variables and dry_run, but no strategy implementation
             reads these fields. variables are substituted in the transform
             phase before strategies are called; dry_run is already handled in
             the build command before strategies are invoked. Both fields are
             forward-looking design decisions, but they represent dead payload.
Affected   : src/strategies/strategy.rs, src/strategies/{html,pdf,docx}.rs
Impact     : Minor — suppressed by #[allow(dead_code)]; no runtime effect.
Status     : Acknowledged; suppressed in FINDING-03 fix.
Suggested Fix (future): Either remove the fields (breaking API change) or
             implement their intended purpose:
             - dry_run: skip pandoc invocation, log "[dry-run] Would render ..."
             - variables: pass as `--variable key=value` pandoc arguments

FINDING-09 [MINOR]
-------------------
Title      : watch command config argument is positional, not a named flag
Description: The `build` subcommand uses `--config <FILE>` (named flag), while
             the `watch` subcommand accepts `<FILE>` as a positional argument.
             This inconsistency may confuse users switching between commands.
Affected   : src/cli.rs
Impact     : Minor UX inconsistency.
Status     : NOT FIXED
Suggested Fix: Align watch to use `--config <FILE>` for consistency:
  Watch {
      #[arg(long, default_value = "renderflow.yaml", value_name = "FILE")]
      config: String,
      ...
  }

FINDING-10 [MINOR]
-------------------
Title      : input.md example file committed to repository root
Description: A sample input.md is committed at the repository root. While
             useful as a quick-start demo, it may confuse users who clone the
             repo and expect a clean slate.
Affected   : input.md
Impact     : Cosmetic.
Status     : NOT FIXED
Suggested Fix: Move to examples/ or docs/ directory, or add a note to
             README that it is the example input for renderflow.yaml.

FINDING-11 [MINOR]
-------------------
Title      : EmojiTransform replaces emoji with [emoji] placeholder
Description: The EmojiTransform converts all emoji characters to the literal
             string "[emoji]". This is lossy and probably not what users expect.
             Users who include 😀 in their documents will see [emoji] in the
             rendered output.
Affected   : src/transforms/emoji.rs
Impact     : Potential user surprise; lossy data transformation.
Status     : NOT FIXED — requires design decision
Suggested Fix: Either document this behaviour explicitly in README/transforms
             docs, or reconsider the transform (e.g. preserve emoji, or replace
             with Unicode names like "grinning face").

